quence number management, and cookie-based stateless server mode\n\n4. **ssl3ecc.c** (32 KB) - ECC Cipher Suite Operations\n   - Implements Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC) operations for ECDHE key exchange\n   - Key functions: ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams (named curve to EC parameters conversion), ssl3_SendECDHServerKeyExchange (server ECDH key exchange), ssl3_HandleECDHServerKeyExchange (client-side ECDH processing), ssl_CreateECDHEphemeralKeyPair (ephemeral key pair generation), ssl_ImportECDHKeyShare (key share import), ssl3_ComputeECDHKeyHash (ECDH key hash computation)\n   - Provides ECC-based cipher suite support for both TLS 1.2 and earlier versions, including ECDHE and ECDH operations\n\n5. **sslexp.h** (57 KB) - Experimental SSL APIs Header\n   - Declares experimental and advanced SSL/TLS functions not guaranteed to remain in future NSS versions\n   - Key declarations: SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro (for dynamic function invocation), SSLExtensionSupport enum (extension support levels), SSL_GetExtensionSupport function (extension capability detection), HPKE support functions\n   - Provides extension point for advanced features while maintaining API stability guarantees for stable APIs\n\nThese files collectively implement the complete TLS protocol stack in NSS, from basic record layer processing (ssl3con.c, tls13con.c) to specialized protocols (dtlscon.c) and cryptographic operations (ssl3ecc.c), with experimental extensions for forward compatibility (sslexp.h)."
